lines.value: the bnf had the problem that options and repetitions could not be directly expressed

lines.value: the fourth chapter of this treatise includes an exposition of the method of least squares a remarkable testimony to laplace's command over the processes of analysis
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in 1805 legendre had published the method of least squares making no attempt to tie it to the theory of probability
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in 1809 gauss had derived the normal distribution from the principle that the arithmetic mean of observations gives the most probable value for the quantity measured then turning this argument back upon itself he showed that if the errors of observation are normally distributed the least squares estimates give the most probable values for the coefficients in regression situations
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: these two works seem to have spurred laplace to complete work toward a treatise on probability he had contemplated as early as 1783
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in two important papers in 1810 and 1811 laplace first developed the characteristic function as a tool for large sample theory and proved the first general central limit theorem
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: then in a supplement to his 1810 paper written after he had seen gauss's work he showed that the central limit theorem provided a bayesian justification for least squares if one were combining observations each one of which was itself the mean of a large number of independent observations then the least squares estimates would not only maximise the likelihood function considered as a posterior distribution but also minimise the expected posterior error all this without any assumption as to the error distribution or a circular appeal to the principle of the arithmetic mean
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in 1811 laplace took a different non bayesian tack
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: considering a linear regression problem he restricted his attention to linear unbiased estimators of the linear coefficients
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: after showing that members of this class were approximately normally distributed if the number of observations was large he argued that least squares provided the best linear estimators
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: here it is best in the sense that it minimised the asymptotic variance and thus both minimised the expected absolute value of the error and maximised the probability that the estimate would lie in any symmetric interval about the unknown coefficient no matter what the error distribution
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: his derivation included the joint limiting distribution of the least squares estimators of two parameters
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the meaning of the various bids in a partnership are called that partnership's bidding system

lines.value: a number of different bidding systems exist such as goren acol standard american and precision club

lines.value: many experts today use a system called two over one 2/1 game forcing

lines.value: bids doubles redoubles and even passes can be either natural or conventional
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a natural bid is a proposal to reach a contract in the named suit
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a conventional bid is an attempt to communicate offering and or asking for information about the partnerships hands
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a natural suit bid is one that implies some length in the suit bid
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: for example an opening bid of one spade showing at least 5 cards in spades and nothing about any other suit lengths would be natural
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a conventional suit bid provides information unrelated to the suit named
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: for example an opening bid of one club showing 16 or more points but saying nothing about how many clubs are held would be conventional
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a natural notrump bid is one that implies a balanced distribution of cards among all suits generally distributions of 4-3-3-3 4-4-3-2 and 5-3-3-2 cards although some players will treat other hand patterns as balanced and a certain number of points as agreed upon by the partnership
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a conventional notrump bid says none of these things
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the most common examples of conventional notrump bids are the unusual notrump showing length in 2 unbid suits and the blackwood convention
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a natural double also called penalty is one that implies an intent to defend and defeat the current contract
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a conventional double is one that conveys some other meaning
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the most common example of a conventional double is the takeout double of a low level bid implying support for the unbid suits and asking partner to choose one of them
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a forcing bid is one that by agreement requires partner to give the bidder another chance to bid
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: unless the bidder's left hand opponent bids the partner promises to make a bid

lines.value: a common example of such a treatment is the forcing notrump as well as all the conventions listed below

lines.value: some of the most famous are stayman jacoby transfers and blackwood

lines.value: the player who wins the trick leads to the next one

lines.value: the player from the pair that won the bidding that is the pair that is going to play the contract who was the first to make a bid in the suit of the final contract who is thus either the player bidding the final contract or his partner is called the declarer

lines.value: his partner is called the dummy

lines.value: after the first card has been played the dummy lays his cards open on the table

lines.value: these cards are from then on played by the declarer who plays dummy's cards whenever it is the dummy's turn to play on a trick

lines.value: the dummy does nothing else for the remainder of the hand hence the term

lines.value: apart from this the play is just like other trick taking games the player who took the previous trick leads to the next one if the declarer took the trick in dummy he has to play from dummy on the next trick if he took the trick in his own hand he has to play from his own hand

lines.value: there are two major systems pairs and teams games
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in friendly play one generally plays rubber bridge
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in rubber bridge extra points are scored for winning a rubber which means getting to a game 100 points twice
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: there are two types of points points below the line and points above the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: only points below the line count towards a game
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if the declarer makes his contract the number bid multiplied by a suit dependent multiplier is scored below the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: any overtricks again multiplied by the suit dependent multiplier are scored above the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the multiplier is 20 for clubs and diamond the minor suits and 30 for hearts and spades the major suits
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: for no trump the multiplier is also 30 but with an added 10 points below the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: examples
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if the score of a partnership below the line equals or exceeds 100 points either at once or taken together with what already was below the line the partnership is said to have scored a game and all scores below the line are turned into scores above the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: thus making game takes five tricks in a minor suit four in a major suit or three in no trump or some combination of partial scores
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the first partnership that wins two games wins the rubber
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: they score a 700 point bonus if they won in two games or 500 points if their opponents also made a game
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a partnership that has already made a game is called vulnerable which is of importance for the slam bonus and for the downtricks
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if a player bids and makes a contract of 6 in something i.e wins all but one trick he is said to have made a small slam
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this gives a bonus above the line of 500 points when not vulnerable and 750 points when vulnerable
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if a player bids and makes a contract of 7 in something thus scoring all the tricks he is said to have made a grand slam
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this gives a bonus of 1000 points when not vulnerable and 1500 points when vulnerable
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if a pair goes down their opponents score points above the line
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if the pair is not vulnerable their opponents get 50 points per undertrick if it is vulnerable 100 points per undertrick
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if a pair is doubled and makes their contract they get double points for all tricks bid while overtricks score extra 100 points per overtrick if not vulnerable 200 points if vulnerable
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: furthermore the pair gets 50 points bonus for the insult
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: all these values are doubled again if the contract was redoubled
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the slam bonuses are not influenced by a double nor are the rubber bonuses although the latter are of course influenced by the fact that there are more scores below the line and thus games are reached faster
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if a pair is doubled and goes down the penalty points to the other pair are as follows
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if you read old bridge books you may notice some differences in the scoring rules
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the undertrick penalty when doubled not vulnerable used to be 100 for the first undertrick and 200 for each subsequent
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this was changed because it was too easy to sacrifice against a grand slam
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a vulnerable grand slam is worth 1500 slam bonus + 500 game bonus + 210 major suit trick score = 2210
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: down 11 doubled not vulnerable used to be 2100 a profitable sacrifice
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: also the insult bonus for making a redoubled contract used to be only 50
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this was changed to 100 so that playing 5 of a minor redoubled making an overtrick is always worth more than an undoubled small slam
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in duplicate bridge which is what is normally played in a club or tournament each hand is scored by itself and not as part of a rubber
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this changes and simplifies the scoring as described above
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in duplicate bridge if the required number of tricks for the contract has been made the pair gets a number of points for the tricks bid and the overtricks as described above 20 per trick above the book of six tricks in clubs diamonds 30 per trick in hearts spades 30 per trick plus 10 bonus in no trump possibly doubled or redoubled
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if the number actually bid is enough to score 100 points or more a game has been made which scores 300 when not vulnerable and 500 when vulnerable
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: if it is lower the score is not carried over to the next hand but there is a part score bonus of 50 points
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the bonus for slam the bonus for the insult and the scores for downtricks and doubled overtricks are the same as described above
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in duplicate bridge in every series of four deals the vulnerabilities of all vulnerable none vulnerable vulnerable against not vulnerable and not vulnerable against vulnerable will all occur once in a predetermined order
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in tournaments bidding boxes are frequently used
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a bidding box is a box of cards each bearing the name of one of the legal calls in bridge
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: a player wishing to make a call displays the appropriate card from the box rather than making a verbal declaration
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: this prevents unauthorized information from being conveyed via voice inflection
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: in top national and international events bidding screens are used
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: these are diagonal screens which are placed across the table preventing a player from seeing his partner during the game
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: there are several free and some subscription based servers available for playing bridge on the internet
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: okbridge 1 is the oldest of the internet bridge services players of all standards from beginners to world champions may be found playing there
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: swan games 2 is a more recent competitor
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: the american contract bridge league the english bridge union and the dutch bridge union also have internet bridge services
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: yahoo games also has several online rubber bridge rooms
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: among the free servers bridge base online is notable for enforcing a high standard of ethics
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: many world class players may be found there
lines.name: Ukrainian

lines.value: there are many advantages to playing bridge online
lines.name: Ukrainian
